00:00:01.536 --> 00:00:05.632
<b>Fortunately, there is an easy way to position your body for strength and balance.</b>

00:00:05.888 --> 00:00:08.960
<b>We call this technique Same Side Hand and Foot.</b>

00:00:09.472 --> 00:00:11.008
<b>If you are reaching with your right hand,</b>

00:00:11.264 --> 00:00:13.056
<b>what foot should be forward? </b>
<b>Easy. </b>

00:00:13.312 --> 00:00:14.080
<b>Your right foot.</b>

00:00:14.592 --> 00:00:16.384
<b>And if you are reaching with your left hand?</b>

00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:18.944
<b>Improve your leverage and reduce twist</b>

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:20.736
<b>by putting your left foot forward.</b>

00:00:21.504 --> 00:00:23.552
<b>But what if you are reaching with both hands?</b>

00:00:23.808 --> 00:00:26.112
<b>The technique would be to put one foot forward,</b>

00:00:26.368 --> 00:00:26.880
<b>or</b>

00:00:27.136 --> 00:00:29.952
<b>back to line up for both balance and strength.</b>

